page.content: the village in 1965 and said that the village had doubled in size since then,and that the numbers of cars had increased dramatically.He said that the other major change was in the nature of the shops in the{High St. Where once there had been shops to serve the local community now there were only shops to cater for the tourists.Many people that we interviewed expressed the same regret and were concerned that older residents had to go up to the{Rise}for basic shopping.The rail services had decreased with the closure of the line which used to run through{Bourne End to High Wycombe.The interior of the {Church}had changed considerably and there were many more people now attending the services.Many people felt that the car park on the{Moor}was a change for the worse.
